Sorry, I left something.
Ms Ohno gave me a key.

524
00:47:41,899 --> 00:47:45,068
Well, you're working late.

525
00:48:07,590 --> 00:48:08,842
Did you...

526
00:48:10,426 --> 00:48:13,763
put those flowers
in my counselling room?

527
00:48:14,222 --> 00:48:15,932
You noticed?

528
00:48:16,474 --> 00:48:19,936
No one else bothers.
You like flowers, right?

529
00:48:24,023 --> 00:48:26,442
I use this to cut the flowers.

530
00:48:27,902 --> 00:48:28,945
Doctor?

531
00:48:31,072 --> 00:48:32,615
Thank you.

532
00:48:33,324 --> 00:48:35,034
I appreciate it but please don't

533
00:48:35,451 --> 00:48:36,869
enter my office without permission.

534
00:48:37,203 --> 00:48:38,245
Why?

535
00:48:38,329 --> 00:48:39,580
Please stop!

536
00:48:40,331 --> 00:48:41,498
That's not what I mean.

537
00:48:42,249 --> 00:48:44,877
Then why are you backing away?

538
00:48:45,878 --> 00:48:48,589
Why are you afraid of me?

539
00:48:48,672 --> 00:48:49,840
That's not it!

540
00:48:50,340 --> 00:48:51,592
What?

541
00:48:51,842 --> 00:48:53,552
You're acting strange!

542
00:48:53,635 --> 00:48:55,470
You kept me waiting.

543
00:48:55,554 --> 00:48:58,432
Isn't it rude to keep me waiting?

544
00:48:58,515 --> 00:49:00,851
Ms Kurahashi! Keep calm.

545
00:49:00,934 --> 00:49:02,727
I'm not mad!

546
00:49:02,811 --> 00:49:05,564
I don't mean
to overlook your kindness.

547
00:49:05,647 --> 00:49:07,941
I said I'm not mad!

548
00:49:08,024 --> 00:49:12,028
Why am I so mad at you?
Don't be conceited!

549
00:49:14,572 --> 00:49:16,616
I was so kind to you.

550
00:49:17,450 --> 00:49:20,370
Why do you make me feel like this?

551
00:50:03,328 --> 00:50:05,289
Are you all right?

552
00:50:07,499 --> 00:50:09,584
Come on!

553
00:50:14,923 --> 00:50:15,966
Wake up.

554
00:50:25,600 --> 00:50:27,644
Come on, please.

555
00:50:28,561 --> 00:50:29,729
Wake up.

556
00:51:40,006 --> 00:51:41,758
Sadako...

557
00:51:52,852 --> 00:51:55,896
Come on! Hurry!

558
00:52:21,713 --> 00:52:22,839
Akikawa!

559
00:52:23,632 --> 00:52:24,800
Akikawa!

560
00:52:26,635 --> 00:52:27,969
What's the matter?

561
00:52:28,720 --> 00:52:29,846
Wake up.

562
00:52:29,930 --> 00:52:31,556
Are you okay?

563
00:52:31,640 --> 00:52:32,682
Akikawa!

564
00:52:32,766 --> 00:52:34,434
I'll take her to ICU!

565
00:52:35,060 --> 00:52:36,186
Akikawa!

566
00:52:37,020 --> 00:52:38,063
Hey!

567
00:52:39,397 --> 00:52:40,565
You okay?

568
00:52:41,232 --> 00:52:43,193
- Hey!
- Ms Kurahashi!

569
00:52:44,569 --> 00:52:47,905
Ms Kurahashi, what happened?

570
00:52:48,406 --> 00:52:50,074
Ms Kurahashi,
I'd like to examine you.

571
00:52:50,158 --> 00:52:51,701
Can you stand up?

572
00:52:52,952 --> 00:52:53,995
Let's stand up.

573
00:52:54,996 --> 00:52:57,790
What's wrong? Please calm down!

574
00:52:58,457 --> 00:53:00,042
Get a wheelchair!

575
00:53:00,376 --> 00:53:01,502
It's okay.

576
00:53:01,585 --> 00:53:05,214
Got it, I won't touch you.
It's all right. Calm down.

577
00:53:05,297 --> 00:53:06,424
Look, it's all right.

578
00:53:07,466 --> 00:53:10,177
Let's get on the wheelchair.

579
00:53:34,326 --> 00:53:36,870
Ms Kurahashi has been admitted.

580
00:53:38,371 --> 00:53:40,123
Her condition was improving,
but now...

581
00:53:42,834 --> 00:53:43,960
I'm sorry.

582
00:53:44,544 --> 00:53:45,962
It's not your fault.

583
00:53:53,303 --> 00:53:55,054
You need a break.

584
00:53:56,597 --> 00:53:57,849
You need to take care of yourself

585
00:53:57,932 --> 00:53:59,183
before you can take care
of your patients.

586
00:53:59,267 --> 00:54:00,852
How's the girl?

587
00:54:03,187 --> 00:54:04,480
She's still in ICU.

588
00:54:13,948 --> 00:54:15,324
And still unconscious.

589
00:54:15,658 --> 00:54:18,661
Honestly, it doesn't look good.

590
00:54:24,541 --> 00:54:25,668
Mr Fujii.

591
00:54:29,880 --> 00:54:30,964
I...

592
00:54:31,507 --> 00:54:33,383
I saw something weird.

593
00:54:37,679 --> 00:54:39,723
When Ms Kurahashi attacked me.

594
00:54:44,060 --> 00:54:45,896
I saw a woman with long hair.

595
00:55:40,782 --> 00:55:42,367
You are Sadako.

596
00:55:43,160 --> 00:55:45,412
The reincarnation of Sadako.

597
00:55:50,709 --> 00:55:53,128
You are a harbinger of misfortune.

598
00:55:54,379 --> 00:55:56,881
You are destined to take life...

599
00:55:58,049 --> 00:55:59,509
as did Sadako!

600
00:57:03,154 --> 00:57:04,364
Sadako.

601
00:57:07,909 --> 00:57:09,160
Dr Akikawa!

602
00:57:10,328 --> 00:57:12,497
She can't talk now.

603
00:57:13,414 --> 00:57:14,457
Doctor!

604
00:57:15,250 --> 00:57:17,585
Please, don't. Doctor!

605
00:57:25,301 --> 00:57:28,346
I'm here to talk about Sadako.

606
00:57:31,015 --> 00:57:32,433
Please tell me.

607
00:57:33,684 --> 00:57:35,519
My brother is missing.

608
00:57:38,272 --> 00:57:41,066
He has probably seen her too.

609
00:57:41,650 --> 00:57:42,818
Ms Kurahashi

610
00:57:42,902 --> 00:57:45,446
you called that thing Sadako.

611
00:57:46,113 --> 00:57:49,491
Please tell me! What is she?

612
00:57:59,876 --> 00:58:01,503
When I was in high school

613
00:58:03,088 --> 00:58:04,798
my friend died.

614
00:58:07,342 --> 00:58:08,927
Not just her.

615
00:58:10,554 --> 00:58:12,472
Many people did.

616
00:58:14,266 --> 00:58:15,475
All of them...

617
00:58:16,393 --> 00:58:17,852
got killed.

618
00:58:20,939 --> 00:58:22,482
It was the curse of Sadako.

619
00:58:24,901 --> 00:58:26,027
Curse?

620
00:58:28,780 --> 00:58:29,989
A long time ago

621
00:58:31,574 --> 00:58:34,118
a psychic killed herself.

622
00:58:36,078 --> 00:58:37,788
She was clairvoyant.

623
00:58:38,998 --> 00:58:41,417
Her reputation grew gradually.

624
00:58:43,002 --> 00:58:46,881
One day, she was maligned
and labelled a fraud.

625
00:58:48,007 --> 00:58:49,467
Because of that...

626
00:58:50,384 --> 00:58:52,344
she killed herself.

627
00:58:55,514 --> 00:58:57,099
Her daughter was...

628
00:58:59,601 --> 00:59:00,811
Sadako.

629
00:59:03,647 --> 00:59:04,940
With just a thought

630
00:59:06,733 --> 00:59:08,777
Sadako could strike a person dead.

631
00:59:10,988 --> 00:59:13,031
She was far more powerful
than her mother.

632
00:59:19,037 --> 00:59:24,000
Alas, her life ended abruptly.

633
00:59:27,712 --> 00:59:29,839
Fearful of her power

634
00:59:30,507 --> 00:59:32,133
her father threw her...

635
00:59:35,011 --> 00:59:36,054
down a well.

636
00:59:36,429 --> 00:59:39,182
Sadako was tossed away and killed.

637
00:59:44,479 --> 00:59:47,940
That's the origin of the curse.

638
00:59:51,027 --> 00:59:53,487
All who come in contact
with her curse

639
00:59:54,947 --> 00:59:56,282
were killed.

640
00:59:58,367 --> 01:00:00,119
Including my friend.

641
01:00:00,703 --> 01:00:01,829
Everyone.

642
01:00:04,415 --> 01:00:05,666
A curse.

643
01:00:07,459 --> 01:00:08,502
No way.

644
01:00:08,836 --> 01:00:10,712
I have no doubt it was Sadako!

645
01:00:10,879 --> 01:00:15,676
It's true, I tell you!
The curse exists. I've seen it!

646
01:00:48,750 --> 01:00:51,461
It is not possible to save him.

647
01:00:53,880 --> 01:00:55,298
Your brother

648
01:00:56,382 --> 01:00:57,800
has been cursed.

649
01:01:03,597 --> 01:01:05,641
<i>That hurt!</i>

650
01:01:07,726 --> 01:01:09,770
<i>Man, I could hear my back cracking.</i>

651
01:01:10,854 --> 01:01:13,816
<i>Next time for sure! On to round two!</i>

652
01:01:14,024 --> 01:01:16,819
<i>I'll try it backwards. Gently...</i>

653
01:01:21,949 --> 01:01:25,035
<i>There! The Wrinkled Mug!</i>

654
01:01:30,874 --> 01:01:34,336
Where are you, Kazuma?

655
01:01:34,503 --> 01:01:38,465
<i>This was Fantastic Kazuma!
Subscribe to my channel!</i>

656
01:02:14,500 --> 01:02:15,709
Kazuma?

657
01:02:51,786 --> 01:02:52,954
Hello?

658
01:02:53,997 --> 01:02:56,374
<i>It's Ishida. Sorry to call suddenly.</i>

659
01:02:58,084 --> 01:02:59,627
I found Kazuma.

660
01:03:00,962 --> 01:03:04,632
He's in the video
we uploaded earlier.

661
01:03:05,466 --> 01:03:06,509
<i>I know.</i>

662
01:03:10,429 --> 01:03:13,891
I saw the video too.

663
01:04:44,313 --> 01:04:45,439
Oshima?

664
01:04:46,064 --> 01:04:48,233
Yes, Oshima Island in Izu.

665
01:04:48,859 --> 01:04:52,195
I did an image search.
I think it's correct.

666
01:04:53,321 --> 01:04:56,616
It's a place where
mountain ascetics trained.

667
01:04:56,867 --> 01:04:59,411
<i>Mysterious Spots in Tokyo, Izu Cave</i>

668
01:04:59,870 --> 01:05:03,164
Many priests lost their lives here.

669
01:05:04,207 --> 01:05:07,961
The shrine was built
to appease their souls.

670
01:05:09,337 --> 01:05:13,299
But a cave-in made it off-limits
for the past 20 years.

671
01:05:16,886 --> 01:05:18,930
Do you recognise this talisman?

672
01:05:24,811 --> 01:05:26,312
<i>It's got a chain.</i>

673
01:05:26,938 --> 01:05:28,564
<i>Should I open the closet?</i>

674
01:05:30,274 --> 01:05:31,734
<i>Whoa! Huh?</i>

675
01:05:31,817 --> 01:05:33,569
<i>They are talismans!</i>

676
01:05:39,825 --> 01:05:40,993
Like the complex?

677
01:05:42,202 --> 01:05:44,663
Sofue was connected to this place.

678
01:05:46,290 --> 01:05:47,583
What does that mean?

679
01:05:48,459 --> 01:05:49,626
I don't know.

680
01:05:50,669 --> 01:05:53,338
First of all,
how was the video uploaded?

681
01:05:56,717 --> 01:05:57,759
<i>I think</i>

682
01:05:58,719 --> 01:06:02,180
<i>this is an incredible find and...</i>

683
01:06:05,267 --> 01:06:07,185
I first saw it here.

684
01:06:08,562 --> 01:06:11,231
Do you know about the cursed video?

685
01:06:12,023 --> 01:06:13,066
What?

686
01:06:13,566 --> 01:06:16,027
It was all over the Internet.

687
01:06:16,694 --> 01:06:19,572
I don't know who found it first

688
01:06:20,240 --> 01:06:24,494
but at some point, it was mixed in
with other videos.

689
01:06:25,161 --> 01:06:28,748
Then, a rumour started saying that

690
01:06:28,831 --> 01:06:30,958
the video creators were cursed.

691
01:06:32,877 --> 01:06:33,961
A curse...

692
01:06:34,962 --> 01:06:37,006
It's just an urban legend.

693
01:06:49,226 --> 01:06:52,563
"The psychic, Yamamura Shizuko

694
01:06:53,480 --> 01:06:55,274
to be publicly tested."

695
01:06:55,733 --> 01:06:57,109
Supernatural powers?

696
01:07:06,451 --> 01:07:08,370
Is this the woman in the video?

697
01:07:10,455 --> 01:07:13,291
The psychic
who killed herself was real.

698
01:07:14,042 --> 01:07:15,085
What?

699
01:07:16,628 --> 01:07:18,672
She was born on Oshima Island.

700
01:07:19,214 --> 01:07:21,841
Sadako must have been too.

701
01:07:23,009 --> 01:07:24,135
Sadako?

702
01:07:28,598 --> 01:07:29,849
Kazuma is...

703
01:07:30,433 --> 01:07:31,851
in Oshima.

704
01:07:42,737 --> 01:07:43,905
Hello?

705
01:07:44,322 --> 01:07:46,240
Hello, this is Fujii.

706
01:07:49,035 --> 01:07:50,578
Don't be alarmed but...

707
01:07:52,037 --> 01:07:53,622
Ms Kurahashi has died.

708
01:07:54,623 --> 01:07:55,666
What?

709
01:07:55,875 --> 01:07:59,253
When the nurse found her
this morning, she was already...

710
01:07:59,837 --> 01:08:01,338
One, two, three!

711
01:08:18,688 --> 01:08:19,898
What is it?

712
01:08:21,024 --> 01:08:22,651
I must save Kazuma.

713
01:08:22,859 --> 01:08:24,402
Wait, you mean...

714
01:08:29,741 --> 01:08:30,784
Mayu!

715
01:08:33,995 --> 01:08:35,163
I'll go with you.

716
01:08:36,122 --> 01:08:38,249
I got Kazuma into this.

717
01:09:11,323 --> 01:09:12,783
Aren't you cold?

718
01:09:14,660 --> 01:09:16,119
Let's go inside.

719
01:09:27,756 --> 01:09:29,966
What was it Kazuma saw?

720
01:09:31,760 --> 01:09:34,679
The last time we met

721
01:09:35,221 --> 01:09:36,765
he said he'd seen it.

722
01:09:40,852 --> 01:09:42,562
Kazuma became cursed.

723
01:09:44,022 --> 01:09:46,649
Do you really believe in curses?

724
01:09:47,275 --> 01:09:48,735
I saw her too.

725
01:09:50,028 --> 01:09:51,154
Sadako.

726
01:09:59,412 --> 01:10:00,746
At the complex

727
01:10:01,163 --> 01:10:03,040
he saw Sadako

728
01:10:06,001 --> 01:10:09,213
in the room
where the girl was imprisoned.

729
01:10:14,593 --> 01:10:17,638
A girl who shared
the same fate as Sadako

730
01:10:20,015 --> 01:10:22,309
has resurrected the curse.

731
01:11:02,265 --> 01:11:03,307
Let's go.

732
01:11:09,313 --> 01:11:11,315
<i>No large tents
are allowed in the area</i>

733
01:11:11,399 --> 01:11:13,442
<i>Oshima Fisherman's Union</i>

734
01:11:13,526 --> 01:11:16,654
<i>Keep Out</i>

735
01:11:27,748 --> 01:11:29,083
Please wait here.

736
01:11:32,211 --> 01:11:33,629
Hold it there!

737
01:11:34,463 --> 01:11:35,839
What are you doing?

738
01:11:36,673 --> 01:11:39,426
Hold it! Can't you read?

739
01:11:39,509 --> 01:11:42,763
My brother is in the cave shrine.

740
01:11:43,221 --> 01:11:45,515
Please, we have to save him.

741
01:11:45,599 --> 01:11:46,641
What?

742
01:12:08,830 --> 01:12:10,665
Is someone in the cave?

743
01:12:13,584 --> 01:12:16,712
This isn't a place for sightseeing.

744
01:12:18,089 --> 01:12:21,592
You have no idea what this place is.

745
01:12:24,678 --> 01:12:26,722
Many were swept away from

746
01:12:27,473 --> 01:12:29,642
the banks of this sacred shore.

747
01:12:30,935 --> 01:12:32,978
Those that are unwanted

748
01:12:33,604 --> 01:12:35,773
are washed away by the sea.

749
01:12:37,191 --> 01:12:38,358
Infanticide.

750
01:12:41,653 --> 01:12:42,863
Unwanted babies

751
01:12:44,531 --> 01:12:46,616
were put in the shrine and

752
01:12:47,159 --> 01:12:48,994
carried out to sea.

753
01:12:50,579 --> 01:12:51,746
Souls of children

754
01:12:52,664 --> 01:12:56,126
killed by their parents
gather in the shrine.

755
01:12:58,503 --> 01:13:00,380
Sadako thrives on them.

756
01:13:02,757 --> 01:13:03,883
Sadako.

757
01:13:04,843 --> 01:13:06,845
Do you know Yamamura Sadako?

758
01:13:08,638 --> 01:13:10,181
It's impossible today.

759
01:13:10,723 --> 01:13:11,975
It's the spring tide.

760
01:13:12,684 --> 01:13:13,768
Spring tide?

761
01:13:14,644 --> 01:13:16,729
Tonight is the full moon.

762
01:13:17,647 --> 01:13:19,065
It will be high tide.

763
01:13:20,399 --> 01:13:24,528
Go in there and
the sea will drag you down.

764
01:13:38,959 --> 01:13:40,044
The full moon.

765
01:13:41,086 --> 01:13:42,129
Of course.

766
01:13:43,422 --> 01:13:44,465
Look.

767
01:13:50,304 --> 01:13:52,014
The video is changing?

768
01:13:52,681 --> 01:13:53,890
How?

769
01:13:57,102 --> 01:14:02,065
<i>Dangerous cave
Do not enter</i>

770
01:14:08,154 --> 01:14:09,698
We can't go in today.

771
01:14:10,115 --> 01:14:14,285
The tide is getting too high.
Maybe tomorrow...

772
01:14:14,369 --> 01:14:15,954
- It'll be too late!
- Why?

773
01:14:16,037 --> 01:14:17,705
We must go now or he'll be...

774
01:14:17,789 --> 01:14:21,084
It'd only be another disaster.
Please understand.

775
01:14:21,167 --> 01:14:24,337
- Hold on...
- Don't be stupid!

776
01:14:24,629 --> 01:14:26,255
- Calm down!
- Get off!

777
01:14:26,339 --> 01:14:28,299
Calm down!

778
01:14:44,023 --> 01:14:45,524
If the full moon rises

779
01:14:48,235 --> 01:14:49,737
Kazuma will...

780
01:14:50,738 --> 01:14:52,489
Don't be so ominous.

781
01:14:53,866 --> 01:14:56,451
He was always there for me.

782
01:15:01,039 --> 01:15:02,291
Kazuma and I...

783
01:15:04,001 --> 01:15:05,585
grew up in an orphanage.

784
01:15:09,339 --> 01:15:12,384
I was in grade school
when we were abandoned.

785
01:15:23,561 --> 01:15:26,564
What's up, Sis? Not hungry?

786
01:15:40,453 --> 01:15:42,079
Check out my new move!

787
01:15:42,580 --> 01:15:44,707
The wrinkled mug!

788
01:15:59,555 --> 01:16:00,973
Souls of children

789
01:16:02,474 --> 01:16:06,186
killed by their parents
gather in the shrine.

790
01:16:11,233 --> 01:16:12,984
Could it be that Kazuma and I...

791
01:16:16,071 --> 01:16:17,656
have been summoned by Sadako?

792
01:17:17,714 --> 01:17:18,757
Mayu!

793
01:17:50,580 --> 01:17:53,457
<i>Keep Out</i>

794
01:18:40,754 --> 01:18:42,297
Kazuma...

795
01:18:43,339 --> 01:18:44,591
he's behind those rocks.

796
01:18:45,425 --> 01:18:46,885
How did he get in?

797
01:19:22,252 --> 01:19:23,337
Kazuma.

798
01:19:30,302 --> 01:19:31,511
No!

799
01:19:34,973 --> 01:19:36,933
Mayu...!

800
01:19:59,122 --> 01:20:00,164
Dammit.

801
01:20:59,013 --> 01:21:00,140
Kazuma.

802
01:21:03,852 --> 01:21:05,603
Where are you, Kazuma?

803
01:22:09,207 --> 01:22:10,250
Kazuma!

804
01:22:11,376 --> 01:22:12,710
What happened?

805
01:22:13,586 --> 01:22:14,963
Pull yourself together!

806
01:22:16,965 --> 01:22:18,049
Kazuma.

807
01:22:26,182 --> 01:22:27,308
Kazuma!

808
01:22:27,850 --> 01:22:28,976
Hey!

809
01:22:57,879 --> 01:22:59,006
No way...

810
01:23:31,704 --> 01:23:32,872
Sadako.

811
01:23:50,180 --> 01:23:51,557
I'm sorry, Sadako.

812
01:23:55,436 --> 01:23:57,396
It is the only way.

813
01:24:29,135 --> 01:24:31,512
Sadako's mother abandoned her.

814
01:24:34,349 --> 01:24:37,852
But she didn't die. She survived.

815
01:24:40,229 --> 01:24:41,314
That's how

816
01:24:42,398 --> 01:24:44,609
she gained her fearsome powers.

817
01:25:06,255 --> 01:25:07,464
You, too?

818
01:25:08,715 --> 01:25:09,925
Abandoned by your mother?

819
01:25:50,965 --> 01:25:53,801
Pulse: 53,
blood pressure 57/31.

820
01:25:53,884 --> 01:25:55,469
SpO2: 93%.

821
01:25:55,553 --> 01:25:56,637
Status?

822
01:25:56,721 --> 01:25:57,763
Still in a coma.

823
01:25:57,888 --> 01:25:58,931
Vital signs?

824
01:25:59,056 --> 01:26:00,391
Temperature: 35C.

825
01:26:03,060 --> 01:26:05,145
- Blood data?
- How much IV is left?

826
01:26:05,229 --> 01:26:06,397
She's showing signs of cyanosis.

827
01:26:06,480 --> 01:26:07,773
- Not good.
- Add more to the IV.

828
01:26:07,856 --> 01:26:09,858
I will. Take this.

829
01:26:09,942 --> 01:26:11,652
She's starting to asphyxiate.

830
01:26:11,860 --> 01:26:13,654
- Doctor!
- Check SpO2!

831
01:26:13,737 --> 01:26:14,947
Got it.

832
01:26:15,489 --> 01:26:16,532
Legs up!

833
01:26:17,616 --> 01:26:19,201
All right? Hang in there.

834
01:26:19,451 --> 01:26:20,577
Fight!

835
01:26:20,661 --> 01:26:21,787
Hold on. Please!

836
01:26:22,954 --> 01:26:25,165
Stay with us!

837
01:26:34,299 --> 01:26:35,342
No!

838
01:26:40,388 --> 01:26:41,598
Don't give in!

839
01:26:44,017 --> 01:26:45,852
You're not alone!

840
01:26:48,062 --> 01:26:50,356
You have me!

841
01:26:51,441 --> 01:26:53,401
I'll care for you!

842
01:26:54,026 --> 01:26:56,112
I'll never let you die!

843
01:27:22,638 --> 01:27:23,931
Doctor, she's conscious.

844
01:27:25,265 --> 01:27:26,391
Vital signs?

845
01:27:26,475 --> 01:27:27,809
Stabilised.

846
01:27:29,019 --> 01:27:30,520
SpO2 is rising.

847
01:27:31,355 --> 01:27:32,397
Blood pressure?

848
01:27:32,564 --> 01:27:34,900
118/79. Stabilising.

849
01:27:36,193 --> 01:27:37,903
Her colour has returned.

850
01:29:11,994 --> 01:29:13,037
Mayu!

851
01:29:14,288 --> 01:29:15,414
Are you all right?

852
01:29:24,090 --> 01:29:25,132
Wait here.

853
01:29:25,216 --> 01:29:26,258
Kazuma!

854
01:29:27,051 --> 01:29:28,636
Hey, Kazuma!

855
01:29:28,802 --> 01:29:30,221
Are you okay, Kazuma?

856
01:29:30,304 --> 01:29:34,183
Kazuma! Snap out of it!

857
01:29:34,266 --> 01:29:36,268
Kazuma! What's happened to you?

858
01:29:37,061 --> 01:29:38,979
Hey, Kazuma!

859
01:29:39,646 --> 01:29:41,982
Kazuma, what's wrong?

860
01:29:42,399 --> 01:29:43,775
Come on!

861
01:29:44,568 --> 01:29:46,486
Hey! Kazuma!

862
01:30:14,722 --> 01:30:16,182
Snap out of it!

863
01:30:19,769 --> 01:30:20,895
Kazuma!

864
01:30:24,273 --> 01:30:25,316
Sis!

865
01:30:52,134 --> 01:30:53,260
Sis!

866
01:30:53,760 --> 01:30:54,928
Run!

867
01:30:55,846 --> 01:30:56,972
Get away!

868
01:30:57,931 --> 01:30:59,266
Kazuma!

869
01:30:59,850 --> 01:31:02,269
Sis! Stay back!

870
01:31:02,352 --> 01:31:03,436
Mayu!

871
01:31:09,943 --> 01:31:11,361
Get off!

872
01:31:12,195 --> 01:31:13,446
Kazuma!

873
01:31:17,617 --> 01:31:19,160
Yusuke, take her!

874
01:31:40,681 --> 01:31:41,807
Sis...

875
01:31:42,808 --> 01:31:44,018
Forgive me!

876
01:31:46,186 --> 01:31:47,563
Kazuma!

877
01:31:50,899 --> 01:31:53,527
No, Kazuma!

878
01:31:53,610 --> 01:31:55,779
No!

879
01:31:58,866 --> 01:31:59,950
Mayu!

880
01:32:00,033 --> 01:32:01,076
No!

881
01:32:01,159 --> 01:32:02,202
No!

882
01:32:02,286 --> 01:32:03,328
Mayu!

883
01:32:15,674 --> 01:32:17,842
Kazuma!

884
01:32:17,926 --> 01:32:22,889
<i>Kurokawa Memorial General Hospital</i>

885
01:33:10,018 --> 01:33:11,269
Dr Akikawa.

886
01:33:18,443 --> 01:33:20,028
Before she leaves

887
01:33:21,238 --> 01:33:23,990
she said she wanted to talk to you.

888
01:33:35,335 --> 01:33:36,836
Your voice.

889
01:33:37,587 --> 01:33:38,880
I heard it clearly.

890
01:33:43,176 --> 01:33:46,596
I could come back
all thanks to you.

891
01:33:51,100 --> 01:33:52,351
Thank you.

892
